<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-4453C5EE-52CE-4426-8ED4-94E48B6806DE" version="4" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-4453C5EE-52CE-4426-8ED4-94E48B6806DE" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title "> 1270114 Buffer plate at inside position </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p "> The error is triggered by the buffer plate encoders, when the buffer plate is compressed by the media, because the media is tensioned between the xtran and the pinch in the drawer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Tensioning happens due to a difference in transported media between the xtran roller and the pinch roller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This is a normal scenario in case the roll of media is empty and the media is fixed to the roll core. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The wheel encoder of the pinch ( Media loading drawer 1 pinch 1 encoder (12B5 ;MLO_DRA1_PINCH1_ENC) , Media loading drawer 1 pinch 2 encoder (12B10 ;MLO_DRA1_PINCH2_ENC) ) is used to determine the size of the active roll and therefor the speed of the roll motor and the pinch motor. A discrepancy between the measured size and actual size can result in the buffer plate being compressed and activating the left buffer sensor (15B7; XMS_BUF_LEFT_SE) and/or the right buffer sensor (15B8; XMS_BUF_RIGHT_SE) 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "/><tsCauses id="GUID-5098493F-E711-4B29-8B8C-61BAFA564A91" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> Media is sticky 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-32C35585-DB19-4C12-A2BB-91C230A5A730" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p "> In case media sticks to the roll, not enough media is fed towards the buffer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Verify the media loading components. See 
<xref keyref="12_DIAG_ANALYZE_MEDIA_LOADING" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-443942F3-4AD5-41B2-B2DA-C8021F9E5681.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="tsTroubleshooting"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 12 Analyze the media loading components?>12 Analyze the media loading components</xref> 
